  <brief_title>Correlation of Hepatitis C, Alcoholic Liver Disease, and Renal Failure With Hyperfibrinolysis in Liver Failure</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Scott Allen</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University of Utah</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      1. Further characterize the incidence of hyperfibrinolysis in cirrhotics

        2. Correlate hyperfibrinolysis with

             1. hepatitis C

             2. alcoholic liver disease

             3. the subset of a&amp;b with renal failure with and without dialysis

        3. Better describe the hyperfibrinolytic ROTEM profile in cirrhotics
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
